as well as
714Equationfga1-equation-3.6bisfga1-equation-3.6bis.xml3.6 bisfga1-proposition-4-corollary-2 \operatorname {Ext} _{ \mathcal {O} _X}^p( \mathcal {O} _Y, \Omega _X^n) = \Omega _Y^{n-p}. \tag{3.6 bis}

Let X be a non-singular algebraic variety of dimension n, and let Y be an algebraic subset of dimension q=n-p of X. Let \mathscr { F } be a coherent algebraic sheaf on X with support contained in Y, and let \mathscr { L } be a locally-free algebraic sheaf on X. Then the sheaves \mathscr {E} \kern -1.5pt \mathit {xt} _{ \mathcal {O} _X}^i( \mathscr { F } , \mathscr { L } ) are zero for i<p, and, when i=p, there is a canonical isomorphism
716Equationfga1-equation-3.7fga1-equation-3.7.xml3.7fga1-proposition-5 \mathscr {E} \kern -1.5pt \mathit {xt} _{ \mathcal {O} _X}^p( \mathscr { F } , \mathscr { L } ) = \mathscr {H} \kern -2.5pt \mathit {om} _{ \mathcal {O} _X}( \mathscr { F } , \mathscr {E} \kern -1.5pt \mathit {xt} ^p( \mathcal {O} _X/ \mathfrak {J}, \mathscr { L } )) \tag{3.7}
where \mathfrak {J} denotes an arbitrary sheaf of ideals on X that annihilates \mathscr { F } and has Y as its set of zeros. In particular, if \mathscr { F } is a coherent algebraic sheaf on Y, then
717Equationfga1-equation-3.7bisfga1-equation-3.7bis.xml3.7 bisfga1-proposition-5 \mathscr {E} \kern -1.5pt \mathit {xt} _{ \mathcal {O} _X}^p( \mathscr { F } , \mathscr { L } ) = \mathscr {H} \kern -2.5pt \mathit {om} _{ \mathcal {O} _Y}( \mathscr { F } , \mathscr {E} \kern -1.5pt \mathit {xt} ^p( \mathcal {O} _Y, \mathscr { L } )). \tag{3.7 bis}
Finally, with \mathscr { F } still a coherent algebraic sheaf on Y, the sheaves \mathscr { E } ^i= \mathscr {E} \kern -1.5pt \mathit {xt} _{ \mathcal {O} _X}^{p+i}( \mathscr { F } , \Omega _X^n) do not depend on the choice of immersion of the algebraic space Y into the non-singular algebraic variety X.

Denote by \omega _Y^q the sheaf \operatorname {Ext} _{ \mathcal {O} _X}^p( \mathcal {O} _Y, \Omega _X^n).
Then there is a functorial isomorphism for coherent algebraic sheaves \mathscr { F } on Y:

